  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving MCH in Malawi 2010-13</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Maternal and child mortality rates in Malawi are amongst the highest in the world. Their vulnerability to preventable illnesses are due to a variety of reasons. They include the inaccessibility and quality of health care services, limited knowledge on good healthcare practices, and poor nutrition. This project will work with thousands of mothers and young women to define how both they, and the health service, could contribute to reducing unnecessary deaths.  They will work with health workers, village chiefs and other volunteers to better monitor the health of pregnant women, mothers and young children. Efforts will be made to make health facilities more accessible, and improving quality of ante natal and maternal services. The project will also support women&#x2019;s groups through promoting vegetable farming and other activities, which will improve women and children&#x2019;s nutritional status as well as providing them with an income. For these women, the project will make giving birth safer and improve the chances of their children surviving. It will help them influence and improve the government health service and will promote the extension of this approach to other areas of Malawi.</narrative>
  </description>
